			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>About Us:</strong></p>
<p>
NoWait is a cloud based wait list management and customer engagement service for restaurants.&nbsp; NoWait allows a host to manage the wait list on an iPad and notify guests with a text message when their table is ready.</p>
<p>
<strong>About This Position:</strong></p>
<p>
We are seeking a talented AWS-based Infrastructure Engineer to manage our web hosting infrastructure to ensure performance, and availability as we continue to experience rapid growth.&nbsp; You will be tasked with managing our entire hosting infrastructure across development, staging and production environments. The ideal candidate will have experience designing, configuring and managing high-availability hosting environments that are secure, and scalable.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Own and manage NoWait&#39;s global cloud infrastructure.</li>
<li>
Help design, develop and deploy secure cloud infrastructure for high availability, low latency and scalability across availability zones.</li>
<li>
Develop and implement strategies to automate system installation, configuration, code deployment, and management</li>
<li>
Develop and manage data backup and replication strategies</li>
<li>
Configure and tune all subsystems including firewalls, load balancers, hypervisors, OS, database, storage subsystems, networks, caching systems, etc.</li>
<li>
Work with development and QA teams to develop procedures and test routines to asses infrastructure performance, capacity, and security</li>
<li>
Deploy real time and trend monitoring of system performance and error logging</li>
<li>
Availability to participate in a 24/7 environment including on call responsibilities</li>
<li>
Work with development team on strategies for managing system failures and recovery</li>
<li>
Architect and manage development/staging/production environments</li>
<li>
Provide recommendations to development team on how to improve security, availability, reliability, scalability</li>
<li>
Daily analysis of system error logs, performance issues, and security risks</li>
<li>
Assist with QA testing, and test automation</li>
<li>
Assist with development tasks as time permits</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
5+ years experience</li>
<li>
Advanced Linux system administration with an understanding of all layers of Linux.</li>
<li>
Production cloud-based LAMP (Linux/Apache/MySQL/PHP) in large scale, mission critical environments.</li>
<li>
High availability configurations and replication methodology both from a systems and software perspective.</li>
<li>
Experience developing and deploying real time and trend monitoring of system performance into a production environment.</li>
<li>
Administration experience with MySQL (advanced features such as MySQL replication is a plus)</li>
<li>
Experience with server and code configuration/deployment tools (Chef, Knife, Puppet)</li>
<li>
Web software development experience(preferably HTML, javascript, PHP, MySQL)</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bonus Points</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Familiarity with any of the following technologies: MongoDB, Redis, New Relic, Capistrano.</li>
<li>
Experience in a startup environment.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Benefits:</strong></p>
<p>
NoWait offers a competitive salary and a full list of benefits, including health, vision and dental coverage. You will work in a fun and creative environment with a talented group of individuals that have a passion for changing the world.</p>
]]></description>
