			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Title:&nbsp;&nbsp; Account Manager<br />
Department(s): Sales<br />
Reports To (Title): Vice President of Sales</strong></p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Job Purpose:</strong><br />
A NoWait Account Manager works alongside Leads and Accounts to help them discover NoWait&rsquo;s added value through customization, answering inquiries, and training.&nbsp; By following a weekly process of calls, demonstrations, and emails, the Account Manager coordinates subscription details such as price tier, length, and billing information.&nbsp; On going, each of those subscriptions reports directly to the Account Manager for customizations and questions.</p>
<p>
<strong>Summary of essential job functions:</strong><br />
An Account Manager will:<br />
&bull; Consistently call Leads and Opportunities according to weekly process<br />
&bull; Answer customer inquiries which come by inbound calls, SnapEngage, and general emails<br />
&bull; Have the ability to respond to customer concerns with proper answers<br />
&bull; Meet weekly and quarterly quotas of subscription agreements<br />
&bull; Utilize calls and emails to ensure proper account creation and usage<br />
&bull; Train accounts on how to optimally use NoWait<br />
&bull; Customize messaging and account information<br />
&bull; Facilitate subscription by receiving proper billing and agreement information<br />
&bull; Update Account statuses on the NoWait Admin Page<br />
&bull; Record all Sales and Account Activity in Salesforce.com</p>
<p>
<strong>Skills and Experience Required:</strong><br />
&bull; 2-3 years general sales experience<br />
&bull; 1 year industry sales experience<br />
&bull; Restaurant training<br />
&bull; Success in following a weekly communication plan</p>
<p>
<strong>Minimum Educational Requirements:</strong><br />
&bull; Bachelors in business</p>
]]></description>
