<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Title:&nbsp;&nbsp; Customer Success Manager<br />
Department(s): Sales<br />
Reports To (Title): Vice President of Sales</strong></p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Job Purpose:</strong><br />
A NoWait Customer Success Manager works alongside new and existing Leads and Accounts to help them discover NoWait&rsquo;s added value through customization, answering inquiries, and training.&nbsp; To ensure successful adoption and expansion of NoWait into certain brands, opportunities may call for on-site training and implementation. A Customer Success Manager will be responsible to communicate &ndash; through phone, email, and on-site events &ndash; NoWait&rsquo;s Return On Investment for wider adoption.</p>
<p>
<strong>Summary of essential job functions:</strong><br />
A Customer Success Manager will:<br />
&bull; Utilize calls, emails, and appointments to discover potential growth into existing accounts<br />
&bull; Be considered an expert trainer on all customer-facing aspects of NoWait<br />
&bull; Have the ability to respond to customer concerns with proper answers<br />
&bull; Meet weekly and quarterly quotas<br />
&bull; Train accounts on how to optimally use NoWait<br />
&bull; Customize messaging and account information<br />
&bull; Record all Sales and Account Activity in Salesforce.com</p>
<p>
<strong>Skills and Experience Required:</strong><br />
&bull; 2-3 years general sales experience<br />
&bull; 1 year industry sales experience<br />
&bull; Restaurant training<br />
&bull; Success in following a weekly communication plan</p>
<p>
<strong>Minimum Educational Requirements:</strong><br />
&bull; Bachelors in business</p>
