			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Job Purpose:</strong></p>
<p>
The Billing Manager will manage all day-to-day billing and collections operations, and will manage projects and initiatives to streamline the company&#39;s billing systems and processes. The Billing Manager will have an opportunity to interact with all major functions within the company, including sales, service delivery, product development &amp; engineering, and business information systems.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Responsible for the day-to day billing and collections functions</li>
<li>
Manage and streamline billing and collections systems and processes</li>
<li>
Review and reconcile internal billing reports and resolve any discrepancies and invoicing adjustments</li>
<li>
Reconciliation of credit card receipts, charge-backs, and refunds</li>
<li>
Review and process monthly revenue accruals/JE entries within the billing cycle</li>
<li>
Maintain and update weekly collections report</li>
<li>
Interact with customers and partners, including fielding customer calls in relation to billing inqueries and requests</li>
</ul>
<p>
The position is based in Pittsburgh and reports to the VP Finance.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
One to three years of experience in accounting/finance required, preferably in a billing department, demonstrating knowledge of billing procedures and various automated accounting systems</li>
<li>
Excellent communication skills both verbal and written</li>
<li>
Excellent analytical and problem solving skills</li>
<li>
Ability to manage multiple projects concurrently</li>
<li>
College Degree in accounting/business management preferred</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
